The paper deals with connectivity relations among points in geometric regions, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of finding the minimal distance for a spanning tree among points with uncertain locations is related to approximation algorithms (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
